            <h2>Definition</h2>
            <p>Calories are a measure of energy. Specifically, they are a measure of the amount of energy that is stored
                in food and released when the food is metabolized by the body. Calories are used by the body to fuel
                physical activity, maintain body temperature, and carry out other essential functions.
            </p>

            <h2>Importance of Tracking Calories</h2>
            <p>
                It is important to watch what you eat because consuming too many calories can lead to weight gain and a
                range of health problems associated with obesity, such as diabetes, heart disease, and certain cancers.
                Conversely, consuming too few calories can lead to malnutrition and other health problems. By monitoring
                your calorie intake and making healthy food choices, you can maintain a healthy weight and reduce your
                risk of chronic diseases.
            </p>
        </div>

